import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the overall distribution of unemployment rates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='rate', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="id", y="rate", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    chart.axhline(y=data['rate'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max rate: {data['rate'].max():.2f}")
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('id').mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='id', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate by location?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of unemployment rates over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
